                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1"><locus target="#ir" facs="001">Fol. ir</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1106HolyWomen">Holy Women</ref>Three female saints, with a prostrate patron below</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d3"><locus target="#iir" facs="002">Fol. iir</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1041HolyMen">Holy Men Potrait</ref>Three figures (the three members of the Trinity?), with the patron prostrate below</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2"><locus target="#iv" facs="002">Fol. iv</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1031VirginAndChild">Virgin and Child</ref> two <term type="angel" ana="#"/>s</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d4"><locus target="#iiv" facs="003">Fol. iiv</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1035HolyMan">Holy Man Portrait</ref><persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4585Georgeo">St George of Lydda</persName> and the <term key="dragon" ana="#dragon"/></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d5">    
                      Decorative designs:
                      <locus target="#1r #75v" facs="003 078">folss. 1r, 75v, </locus>, ornamental band;
                      <locus target="#75v #85r #90v #91v" facs="078 087 093 094">75v, 85r, 90v, 91v</locus>, multiple full stops</decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                    <list>
                    <item xml:id="a1"><desc type="OwnershipNote"><locus target="#75v" facs="078">Fol. 75v</locus> mentions the owner Wäldä ʾArägawi (ወልደ፡ አረጋዊ፡) and the scribe Wäldä Maryam (ወልደ፡ ማርያም፡). The scribe is mentioned again on f. 91v.</desc></item>
                    <item xml:id="e1"><desc><locus target="#91v #92r" facs="094">Fols. 91v, 92r</locus>erased text</desc></item>
                    <item xml:id="a2"><desc type="OwnershipNote"><locus target="#92r">Fol. 92r</locus>note written in blue ink <q>“The holy, glorious gospel”</q> followed by (in Amharic) <q>“It is the gospel of Qes ʾƎnyäw ʾAkälu,”</q> with the letters contained in a pattern of circles</desc></item>
                    <item xml:id="e2"><desc><locus target="#92v" facs="095">Fol. 92v</locus>Unconnected writing from various hands and time periods. Most are groups of a few words, but at the top is a six-line text, quite faded, in Amharic.</desc></item>
                    <item xml:id="e3"><desc>Numbered quires 2–10</desc></item>
                    <item xml:id="e4"><desc>
                      Scribal intervention:
                      words of text are written interlinearly <locus target="#4r #12v #21r #22v #34r" facs="006 015 023 025 036">folss. 4r, 12v, 21r, 22v, 34r, </locus>, etc.;
                      erasure markings are visible <locus target="#19v #85v" facs="022 088">19v, 85v, </locus>;
                      text has been removed <locus target="#12v #20r #39r #40r #52v" facs="015 022 041 042 055">12v, 20r, 39r, 40r, 52v</locus>, etc.</desc></item>
                  </list>
                </additions>

                  <bindingDesc>
